This paper proposes the use of a recurrent neural network (RNN) to predict the trajectory of hurricanes, which involves modeling complex and nonlinear weather data. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of an RNN implies that the paper could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also involves data analysis and processing, which could place it in the Scientific Computing (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of publicly available data from the National Hurricane Center, which could suggest that it belongs to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
